{"title": "Guide to Modern Cookery (Le Guide Culinaire) Part I: Fundamental Elements", "description": "<em>Le Guide Culinaire</em> can be regarded as the \u2018Bible\u2019 of modern cooking. It was Escoffier's attempt to codify and streamline the French restaurant food of the day. The original text was printed for the use of professional chefs and kitchen staff; Escoffier's introduction to the first edition explains his intention that the book be used toward the education of the younger generation of cooks. This usage of the book still holds today; many culinary schools still use it as their core textbook. The book overall is 900 pages long and contains over 2500 recipes. Part 1 is 120 pages long and describes the basic principles and techniques required for the chef, including descriptions of more than 250 recipes and preparations. (Summary by Chris Cartwright adapted from Wikipedia)", "duration": 25850, "language": "English", "authors": [{"id": "9856", "name": "Auguste Escoffier "}], "coverArt": "https://archive.org/download/LibrivoxCdCoverArt33/Escoffier_1406.jpg", "copyright_year": "1903", "genres": ["*Non-fiction", "Cooking"], "supporters": [{"role": "Read by", "name": "LibriVox Volunteers"}, {"role": "Book Coordinator", "name": "Chris Cartwright"}, {"role": "Meta Coordinator", "name": "Ruth Golding"}, {"role": "Proof Listener", "name": "Sarah Jennings"}], "sections": [{"section": 0, "title": "Preface", "readers": [7994], "path": "http://www.archive.org/download/guidetomoderncookery1_1406_librivox/guideculinaire_00_escoffier_64kb.mp3", "duration": 950}, {"section": 1, "title": "Chapter I pt 1: Fonds de Cuisine", "readers": [8798], "path": "http://www.archive.org/download/guidetomoderncookery1_1406_librivox/guideculinaire_01_escoffier_64kb.mp3", "duration": 1664}, {"section": 2, "title": "Chapter I pt 2: Fonds de Cuisine", "readers": [8798], "path": "http://www.archive.org/download/guidetomoderncookery1_1406_librivox/guideculinaire_02_escoffier_64kb.mp3", "durat